title: ICE: `type variables should not be hashed: _#0t` -Cincremental=tmp

labels.name: I-ICE
labels.description: Issue: The compiler panicked, giving an Internal Compilation Error (ICE) ❄️

labels.name: T-compiler
labels.description: Relevant to the compiler team, which will review and decide on the PR/issue.

labels.name: S-has-mcve
labels.description: A Minimal Complete and Verifiable Example has been found for this issue

body:
### Code ```Rust pub fn encode_num(n: u32, mut writer: Writer) -> Result<(), Writer::Error> { if n > 15 { encode_num(n / 16, &mut writer)?; } Ok(()) } pub trait ExampleWriter { type Error; } impl<'a, T: ExampleWriter> ExampleWriter for &'a mut T { type Error = T::Error; } struct Error; impl ExampleWriter for Error { type Error = (); } fn main() { encode_num(69, &mut Error).unwrap(); } ``` ### Meta `rustc --version --verbose`: ``` rustc 1.68.0-nightly (d0dc9efff 2022-12-18) binary: rustc commit-hash: d0dc9efff14ac0a1eeceffd1e605e37eeb8362a0 commit-date: 2022-12-18 host: x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu release: 1.68.0-nightly LLVM version: 15.0.6 ``` ### Error output ``` ```
